          "body": "The note that *the Passover, the feast of the Jews, was near* (6:4) is not chronological filler. It governs everything that follows. The bread Jesus multiplies is Passover bread; the wilderness feeding reenacts the Exodus manna; the demand to *eat the flesh and drink the blood* (v. 53) is unmistakably Passover-lamb language (Exodus 12:7-13). Jesus deliberately stays away from Jerusalem's Passover that year and conducts His own Passover at Capernaum — a Passover in which He is both the giver of the meal and the meal itself. The next Passover He attends will be the one at which He is crucified (12:1; 13:1; 19:14)."
