          "body": "John 6 is the *crisis* chapter of the Galilean ministry. It begins with five thousand following (v. 2) and ends with eleven men standing (vv. 67-71, minus Judas). The reduction is by design. Jesus could have kept the crowd by accepting the kingship they offered (v. 15) or by softening the bread-of-life claims when the grumbling began (vv. 41, 52, 61). Instead He intensifies until only those whom the Father has given (v. 37) and granted (v. 65) remain. The closing exchange with Peter (vv. 67-69) is the chapter's pastoral payoff: *Lord, to whom shall we go? You have words of eternal life. We have believed and have come to know that You are the Holy One of God.* Peter does not understand the discourse perfectly — he understands that no other source of life exists, and that is the chapter's required confession."
